review_blob: I had this when I was in Munchen.  What a wonderful Helles bier.  Too bad you cant get it the States, I would be drinking this stuff every day.
For people who hate drinking beer.  The Cool-Aid of beers.

I felt ripped off when I got the 12 pack and found out that each bottle only contained 11 ounces.  Well, since the beer is so bad, I guess I should have felt rewarded.  I almost committed suicide one night because I was stumped on one of the puzzles. To this day I remember that the solution was Moon Over Miami.   Whos ever heard of that one?  You deserve a cookie.  Oh, about the beer, cheap and intoxicating.  Flavor is non existent.  I dont think I can comment on the appearance.  Who in their right mind has ever took the time to pour this mother in a glass?  It could have been black for all I knew.

I just got this recently and had a taste to see what all the hubbub was about.  And I can say that all the hubbub was right on!  A nice new style of beer that I could continue to savor.  Very special category of unique, classic beer.  It was love at first sip.

When you look in the dictionary under hoppy beer, there is a picture of this beer.  You gotta like hoppy beer to appreciate this one.  Very good IPA style in my opinion. 6 pack at the local Bev N More.   I dont know if I recollect correctly, but when I had this at the actual brewpub in Boonville, I thought it was slightly more hoppy.  Overall, mighty flavorful.

PBR! PBR! PBR!  Brings back fond memories of drinking as a youth. I had it recently and it brought a tear to my eye.  Not because of the fond memories but because of the lack of taste.  Flannel shirt, a baseball cap with a Union logo, and a nice worn hugger around a PBR and you feel like you are the king of the trailer park.

Hammer-time, not!  I grew up guzzling this stuff.  Yeah, it has no flavor but when you are a wee child, what do you know?  Its thirst quenching on a blistering day, you could pound one down, and remain half-sane, but as for aroma I would rather smell dirty gym socks, as for flavor I would rather eat my mother in laws cooking.

When I start a drinkin I swear that Fullers griffin starts talking to me, grab another brew.  It has a nice maltiness to it and goes down very well.  Not much aroma, but has a pleasant taste that keeps you going.  Is this considered a session beer?  I could drink this for a few sessions and then some.

One of my favorite ESBs.  Could be a bit hoppier for my taste, but whos complaining (especially when its going down).  When I get a hankerin for it, I get it at the local Bev N Mo.  I also like the other Fullers line as well.  Overall a very, very satisfying ESB.

I wait for this beer every year.  This winter beer has a nice spicy taste and goes down well like all the Anderson Valley line of beers.  You gotta watch out for the alc content though.  I got some chilling in the fridge as we speak.  I think Ill go get it now.
One of my favorite ESBs. Great mouthfeel-- uses local soft water.  Nice hoppiness.  Overall great flavor, something that I could just keep drinking until I pass out.
